<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-10T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-10T23:00:00-05:00" n="31" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–1149: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-11T12:00:00+08:00">January
                                    11, 1949—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 11—3:56 a.
                                m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>73. As possible indication French China policy is comment French
                            Ambassador in discussing Chinese request for mediation (our 61, January
                            8, and 62 January 9) to effect that given repercussions Indochina of
                            Communist regime in China, French interest required supporting any
                            regime in China resisting Communism. This was true, he said, even though
                            eventual collapse such resistance was inevitable as France would at
                            least gain time.</p>
                        <p>Sent Department 73; repeated Paris 1.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>